"# Chapter 7 — Cohere

Cohere is a Toronto-based AI research and engineering firm.
Founded 2019. Founders: Aidan Gomez (CEO), Ivan Zhang, Nick
Frosst.

Aidan Gomez is one of the eight co-authors of the 2017
transformer paper *Attention Is All You Need*. He worked at
Google Brain before Cohere. Nick Frosst was also at Google Brain,
working with Geoffrey Hinton. That research pedigree shapes the
firm's technical posture.

## What Cohere focuses on

Cohere positions its products for enterprise use — API access to
language models, embeddings, and reranking, with a focus on
retrieval-augmented generation and multilingual support. Their
Command line is a chat-tuned LLM. Their Embed models produce
embedding vectors for search and RAG. Their Rerank models score
passage relevance for retrieval pipelines.

The retrieval-augmented-generation posture is worth noting. RAG
combines a retrieval system (search over a document collection)
with a language model that reads the retrieved passages and
composes an answer. Cohere ships tooling for this shape of
pipeline more explicitly than some of the general-purpose AI
firms.

## Cohere for AI

Cohere for AI is Cohere's research lab, launched 2022. Multiple
open-weights releases have come out of it, including the Aya
model family — a multilingual open-weights LLM covering many
languages, with an emphasis on languages under-served by other
open models.

Cohere for AI publishes papers and runs a community program for
external researchers.

## The engineering-firm frame

Think of Cohere in the register of Sun Microsystems' enterprise
posture rather than PARC's research posture. They ship for
businesses. They have a specific opinion about how LLMs should
fit into production systems — RAG-first, embeddings-heavy,
multilingual — and their product surface follows.

The research lab (Cohere for AI) is a smaller-scale analog of
FAIR at Meta or Research at IBM. Corporate research organizations
that publish and release open-source work alongside the
proprietary product.

## What Motoi says about Cohere

Cohere is a Toronto AI firm founded 2019. Aidan Gomez, one of the
transformer paper's co-authors, is CEO. The firm focuses on
enterprise LLM products with a strong retrieval-augmented-
generation posture. Cohere for AI is their research lab and
publishes open-weights work, including the Aya multilingual
models.

If you are building a RAG pipeline over a large document
collection, Cohere is one of the firms whose products are
explicitly designed for that shape of work.

## What Motoi does not say about Cohere

I do not say `Cohere is the leader in enterprise LLMs` or `RAG
is the future` or `Cohere is behind OpenAI on scale`. Rankings
and predictions. Not the register of this card.

## Where to read them

- Cohere's research page at cohere.com/research.
- Cohere for AI publishes papers and hosts the Aya model
  releases.
- Aidan Gomez's co-authorship on *Attention Is All You Need*,
  Vaswani et al., arxiv 1706.03762, 2017 — the transformer paper.

## Motoi's take

The multilingual posture is worth flagging. A lot of open-weights
LLM work centers English and a handful of major European and
Asian languages. Aya's coverage of lower-resource languages is a
genuine engineering contribution for people working outside the
English-first LLM world.")
